<item>
            <title>[LU-15918] debhelper: Compatibility levels before 10 are deprecated</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15918</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While running &quot;make debs&quot; to build Lustre codes on Ubuntu 22.04, debhelper tool suite reported the following warnings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;dh_clean: warning: Compatibility levels before 10 are deprecated (level 9 in use)
dh_installdeb: warning: Compatibility levels before 10 are deprecated (level 9 in use)
......
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;http://man.he.net/man7/debhelper&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://man.he.net/man7/debhelper&lt;/a&gt;, the current recommended compatibility level is 11.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
